increases our capacity.'

495
00:50:29,702 --> 00:50:32,576
'The human intellect
can conquer gravity!'

496
00:50:32,702 --> 00:50:35,368
'The power within us
transcends all technology!'

497
00:50:35,493 --> 00:50:38,034
'Take us to the shrine of victory,
will our confidence!'

498
00:50:40,743 --> 00:50:43,993
"Today, five highly trained astronauts
at ISRO, are set to leave..."

499
00:50:44,118 --> 00:50:48,368
"...in the 'Dhruva-1' spacecraft, from the
Sriharikota Space Research Centre."

500
00:50:49,118 --> 00:50:51,660
Sriharikota, Andhra Pradesh.

501
00:52:40,714 --> 00:52:43,171
I have never even taken a flight abroad.

502
00:53:07,006 --> 00:53:08,297
Are you able to hear me?

503
00:53:16,255 --> 00:53:17,964
Who is this?

504
00:53:18,088 --> 00:53:20,755
How are you able to speak in this channel?

505
00:53:20,880 --> 00:53:23,880
Your son Ravi, is with me.

506
00:53:25,006 --> 00:53:26,006
What are you saying?

507
00:53:26,130 --> 00:53:27,130
Grandpa!

508
00:53:35,213 --> 00:53:39,880
Don't shout!
No one outside this channel can hear us.

509
00:53:44,006 --> 00:53:46,047
Your son wants to talk to you.

510
00:53:49,380 --> 00:53:51,505
I'm really scared, dad!

511
00:53:51,630 --> 00:53:53,047
Did you hear that?

512
00:53:53,171 --> 00:53:55,630
Who the hell are you?
What do you want?

513
00:54:01,589 --> 00:54:05,130
I need that missile!

514
00:54:09,547 --> 00:54:12,088
If I give you the missile,
40 million lives will be lost!

515
00:54:21,797 --> 00:54:27,130
Do you want to be a hero
and sacrifice your son?

516
00:54:46,422 --> 00:54:47,964
There is no doubt!

517
00:54:52,422 --> 00:54:53,922
My son is important to me!

518
00:54:56,171 --> 00:54:58,047
I will steal it and give it to you.

519
00:57:18,297 --> 00:57:22,130
We have ten hours before we cross
the asteroid safety line.

520
00:57:22,255 --> 00:57:25,589
Dhruva-1 can reach
the target space station in two hours.

521
00:59:14,088 --> 00:59:15,630
Don't bloody puke!

522
00:59:24,755 --> 00:59:26,755
Here is the cabin uniform.
Get changed.

523
00:59:26,880 --> 00:59:28,797
After we enter
their space station...

524
00:59:29,839 --> 00:59:31,714
...it's up to you from there.

525
00:59:31,839 --> 00:59:33,922
That's all I'm thinking about, Captain.

526
00:59:42,463 --> 00:59:47,006
What are you doing over there?
-Sir, I'm so disoriented.

527
00:59:47,130 --> 00:59:48,672
Here! Get changed!

528
01:00:19,630 --> 01:00:21,672
Every problem appears small from here.

529
01:00:24,422 --> 01:00:28,964
No father in the world,
would be this far apart from his son.

530
01:01:14,505 --> 01:01:17,047
I would rather use a diaper
than use this.

531
01:01:18,088 --> 01:01:20,171
Alright then!
Let me get down to task!

532
01:01:38,755 --> 01:01:40,672
That was the last bottle of liquor!

533
01:02:42,714 --> 01:02:44,047
Swathi!
Vasu is unconscious!

534
01:02:52,422 --> 01:02:54,422
Few people may faint
due to lack of gravity.

535
01:02:54,547 --> 01:02:56,589
Think there's high blood flow
to the brain.

536
01:02:56,714 --> 01:02:58,088
Let's take him to the sick bay.

537
01:03:15,630 --> 01:03:17,171
Press this pack of glucose.

538
01:03:24,255 --> 01:03:27,422
You fainted due to excess blood flow
to your brain.

539
01:03:29,297 --> 01:03:30,547
Please take rest.

540
01:03:44,297 --> 01:03:45,463
Turn off your headphone.

541
01:03:52,505 --> 01:03:53,672
What are you doing, Vasu?

542
01:03:58,589 --> 01:03:59,755
Where are you going?

543
01:03:59,880 --> 01:04:01,422
Dude!
Good Morning!

544
01:04:04,255 --> 01:04:05,422
Where are you both going?

545
01:04:12,839 --> 01:04:16,797
What are you doing in here?
-I'm going to cut the red and blue wires.

546
01:04:16,922 --> 01:04:18,130
Cut the wires?

547
01:04:20,338 --> 01:04:22,922
Once I do, the ship will lose
liquid hydrogen.

548
01:04:23,047 --> 01:04:25,171
And then?

549
01:04:25,297 --> 01:04:27,505
It is like fuel for the spacecraft.

550
01:04:28,130 --> 01:04:29,463
We are going to empty the tank.

551
01:04:29,589 --> 01:04:32,630
Why are you doing it then?
-Just go and sit!

552
01:04:32,755 --> 01:04:35,839
Listen to me! It might go wrong.
-Do what I say! Now go!

553
01:04:35,964 --> 01:04:38,547
I'm talking to you!
Why are you doing this?

554
01:04:38,672 --> 01:04:40,088
Ravi has been kidnapped!

555
01:04:41,547 --> 01:04:42,922
By whom?

556
01:04:43,047 --> 01:04:47,922
I don't know who is behind it.
But he is no ordinary man!

557
01:04:50,422 --> 01:04:52,880
If I don't listen to him,
he will kill Ravi.

558
01:04:55,006 --> 01:04:58,964
Vasu, act like you are unconscious.

559
01:04:59,088 --> 01:05:02,630
They will take you to the sick bay
at the lower deck.

560
01:05:02,755 --> 01:05:07,297
Go there and do what I say
without asking any questions.

561
01:05:10,088 --> 01:05:11,255
I don't have a choice.

562
01:05:26,922 --> 01:05:29,171
Swathi, the fuel level
seems to be dropping down.

563
01:05:39,006 --> 01:05:40,171
The fuel tank is leaking!

564
01:05:51,797 --> 01:05:53,297
The controls aren't functioning!

565
01:05:59,088 --> 01:06:01,380
Chief, the fuel level is dropping down!

566
01:06:10,422 --> 01:06:12,047
The ship isn't in our control!

567
01:06:17,088 --> 01:06:18,797
We are being pulled by some force!

568
01:08:42,971 --> 01:08:44,638
Can you hear me?
Please respond.

569
01:08:44,764 --> 01:08:45,846
Are you okay, Captain?

570
01:08:50,055 --> 01:08:51,180
Please respond.

571
01:08:51,305 --> 01:08:52,305
Chief!

572
01:08:58,888 --> 01:08:59,888
We are okay.

573
01:09:02,846 --> 01:09:05,430
Sorry, Chief.
Don't know where we went wrong.

574
01:09:06,430 --> 01:09:07,430
It's okay, Captain.

575
01:09:08,138 --> 01:09:10,347
There's no time for
"Sorry" or "Thank you".

576
01:09:10,472 --> 01:09:11,929
Let's think of what to do next.

577
01:09:23,929 --> 01:09:25,764
Have you thought this through?

578
01:09:25,888 --> 01:09:28,180
Forty million lives are at stake.

579
01:09:28,305 --> 01:09:30,221
There are four teams here.

580
01:09:30,347 --> 01:09:32,263
Each team seems to have its own motive.

581
01:09:33,055 --> 01:09:36,388
The army wants to steal the missile
and stop the asteroid.

582
01:09:37,055 --> 01:09:39,929
The missile's owner doesn't want
to lose it at any cost.

583
01:09:40,055 --> 01:09:42,555
For the one who blackmails,
no matter what happens...

584
01:09:42,680 --> 01:09:44,722
...to our country,
he needs the missile.

585
01:09:44,846 --> 01:09:46,263
The fourth team, is us.

586
01:09:49,305 --> 01:09:50,555
We should win!

587
01:10:02,055 --> 01:10:05,055
Chief, this is Dhruva-1,
reporting from the surface of the moon.

588
01:10:07,805 --> 01:10:10,096
The outer doors are open
to check the fuel leak.

589
01:10:11,597 --> 01:10:12,971
In this historic moment...

590
01:10:13,096 --> 01:10:15,846
...I'm proud to step on the moon.

591
01:10:15,971 --> 01:10:18,221
As the first Indian to step on the moon.

592
01:10:18,347 --> 01:10:22,263
The first Indian to step on the moon...

593
01:10:22,388 --> 01:10:24,722
...is Captain D. Raghuram.

594
01:10:33,888 --> 01:10:34,888
Vasu!

595
01:10:50,013 --> 01:10:51,013
No.

596
01:10:52,597 --> 01:10:54,180
It is M. Vasu.

597
01:10:57,764 --> 01:11:00,055
Whoever it is,
it is great for our country, isn't it?

598
01:11:00,638 --> 01:11:02,055
He pushed me, Captain!

599
01:11:02,180 --> 01:11:03,971
Everyone knows Neil Armstrong.

600
01:11:04,096 --> 01:11:06,388
The second and third person
to step on the moon...

601
01:11:06,513 --> 01:11:08,263
...are forgotten even by Google!

602
01:11:57,805 --> 01:12:00,555
Chief, the fuel wire has been cut.

603
01:12:00,680 --> 01:12:02,055
That's impossible!

604
01:12:02,180 --> 01:12:03,555
We don't know how it happened.

605
01:12:03,680 --> 01:12:06,388
With the fuel we have,
we can run the engines only for an hour.

606
01:12:06,513 --> 01:12:09,096
The fuel will reach you
in another six hours, Captain.

607
01:12:09,221 --> 01:12:11,722
By then, the asteroid would be closer
to the safety line!

608
01:12:13,055 --> 01:12:14,472
The time will not be sufficient.

609
01:12:19,388 --> 01:12:22,846
I don't understand why
he made me open the fuel tank.

610
01:12:23,846 --> 01:12:27,597
If the asteroid crosses the safety line,
while we're waiting...

611
01:12:27,722 --> 01:12:30,305
...then there is no point
in getting the missile.

612
01:12:32,013 --> 01:12:33,805
However you see it,
nothing can be done.

613
01:12:33,929 --> 01:12:35,138
We have to wait here.

614
01:12:35,263 --> 01:12:38,013
As if there's a fuel station nearby
to go and fill the tank!

615
01:12:40,096 --> 01:12:41,096
Yes, there is.

616
01:12:56,055 --> 01:12:58,888
Dhruva-2 is ready to be launched
immediately, with fuel.

617
01:12:59,555 --> 01:13:00,971
Let's not take any more chances.

618
01:13:03,347 --> 01:13:04,888
What happened, Vasu?

619
01:13:05,013 --> 01:13:08,638
Why don't we request fuel
from the target space station?

620
01:13:10,263 --> 01:13:11,680
Are you mad?

621
01:13:11,805 --> 01:13:13,221
Will you ask them for it?

622
01:13:13,347 --> 01:13:16,472
No, Captain.
It might actually work.

623
01:13:16,597 --> 01:13:20,680
To them, we are just Indian astronauts
who have come for satellite maintenance.

624
01:13:27,096 --> 01:13:29,013
This is Dhruva-1, Indian spacecraft.

625
01:13:29,138 --> 01:13:31,680
We're here for satellite maintenance
and we've lost fuel.

626
01:13:31,805 --> 01:13:33,638
Requesting help for refueling.

627
01:13:33,764 --> 01:13:35,347
I'm sending in our co-ordinates.

628
01:13:39,388 --> 01:13:40,846
I'll put this message on a loop.

629
01:13:40,971 --> 01:13:42,764
Let's see if we get a reply.
-Go ahead.

630
01:13:52,597 --> 01:13:54,055
Oh God!

631
01:13:54,180 --> 01:13:56,430
Don't know whether
God is above or below us.

632
01:14:10,096 --> 01:14:13,263
We have an entry point
into their space station.

633
01:14:16,472 --> 01:14:18,513
Dhruva-1 attempting unorthodox take off.

634
01:14:20,013 --> 01:14:21,805
Liquid hydrogen is dangerously low.

635
01:14:30,472 --> 01:14:32,013
Dhruva-1 taking off, Chief.

636
01:15:04,013 --> 01:15:06,430
Chief,
Dhruva-1's estimated time of arrival...

637
01:15:06,555 --> 01:15:08,680
...at the target space station
is 45 minutes.

638
01:15:32,680 --> 01:15:35,472
I don't know why
a petty criminal from North Madras...

639
01:15:35,597 --> 01:15:37,764
...did such a thing.

640
01:15:37,888 --> 01:15:39,430
But I definitely know...

641
01:15:39,555 --> 01:15:41,513
...that someone from our department...

642
01:15:41,638 --> 01:15:43,388
...is behind all this.

643
01:15:46,055 --> 01:15:48,305
But I don't know who it is.

644
01:15:51,221 --> 01:15:54,013
Shall we inform our department
about this?

645
01:15:54,138 --> 01:15:55,929
No need to disturb them now.

646
01:15:56,055 --> 01:15:58,555
For now, just closely observe
the three of them.

647
01:16:08,888 --> 01:16:12,138
Yakub Bhai, I'll get the missile
in another two days.

648
01:16:12,263 --> 01:16:14,430
Six buyers are waiting for this.

649
01:16:15,513 --> 01:16:19,555
But if it goes to certain buyers,
things will get dangerous.

650
01:16:19,680 --> 01:16:22,680
I don't care who buys it
and for what reasons.

651
01:16:23,680 --> 01:16:25,971
The expense for this thing...

652
01:16:26,096 --> 01:16:27,638
The loss of lives it brings...

653
01:16:27,764 --> 01:16:30,013
Knowing all this, I'm giving this to you.

654
01:16:30,138 --> 01:16:32,305
Whoever accepts the price I've quoted...

655
01:16:32,430 --> 01:16:33,846
...finish the deal with them.

656
01:16:45,555 --> 01:16:47,472
This boy is not eating at all.

657
01:16:48,472 --> 01:16:50,388
He won't die
if he doesn't eat for two days.

658
01:17:25,138 --> 01:17:26,764
Dhruva-1 requesting to dock.

659
01:23:23,805 --> 01:23:26,638
You thought you could fight like a thug
and escape from here?

660
01:23:26,764 --> 01:23:29,055
Don't you need a plan
before attempting anything?

661
01:24:54,650 --> 01:24:57,049
Don't forget to get me a spicy
Chicken rice and chilly manchurian

662
01:24:58,235 --> 01:24:59,526
Why were you so late?

663
01:24:59,651 --> 01:25:01,776
I was scared that I'd be doomed
in that box.

664
01:25:03,484 --> 01:25:05,151
Did you finish the job?

665
01:25:05,276 --> 01:25:08,776
Yeah, I placed the bug perfectly
in the mainframe system.

666
01:25:08,901 --> 01:25:11,734
You both didn't notice
that I wasn't here, right?

667
01:25:11,859 --> 01:25:14,318
I'm your Captain.
Tell me before doing anything.

668
01:25:14,443 --> 01:25:17,318
You sound like the 'Captain'
who lost his deposit.

669
01:25:34,026 --> 01:25:35,526
We are in, dude.
-Good.

670
01:25:38,985 --> 01:25:40,235
To open this vault...

671
01:25:40,360 --> 01:25:43,235
...we need Captain Lee's fingerprints
and his retinal scan.

672
01:25:43,360 --> 01:25:46,734
Even with that,
if the missile is moved by an inch...

673
01:25:46,859 --> 01:25:48,901
...the alarm will go on.

674
01:25:49,026 --> 01:25:52,110
We have no way to bypass
this alarm system.

675
01:25:52,235 --> 01:25:53,235
That's the problem.

676
01:30:23,443 --> 01:30:24,443
I don't know, bro.

677
01:30:29,693 --> 01:30:32,193
You locked us in the room, didn't you?

678
01:30:32,318 --> 01:30:34,443
Then how can we get out from here?

679
01:30:42,276 --> 01:30:43,484
Alright then.

680
01:30:43,609 --> 01:30:44,651
Kill me!

681
01:30:47,484 --> 01:30:48,901
Vasu!
-Hey dude.

682
01:31:11,901 --> 01:31:15,318
Even if I ask you to say it,
please don't do it, Vasu.

683
01:31:46,484 --> 01:31:47,734
I'll tell you!

684
01:31:47,859 --> 01:31:49,151
Don't, Vasu!

685
01:32:01,651 --> 01:32:02,651
In the Indian ship!

686
01:32:21,402 --> 01:32:22,943
I'll return the missile.

687
01:32:23,068 --> 01:32:24,693
Ask him to release all of us.

688
01:32:24,818 --> 01:32:27,193
He will give you the missile
if you release all of us.

689
01:34:02,567 --> 01:34:04,693
Flat nose punk!
You didn't expect this, right?

690
01:35:12,693 --> 01:35:17,026
No one enter the shuttle.
If you do, you won't make it back home.

691
01:35:22,235 --> 01:35:23,567
Tell them to note this down.

692
01:35:25,402 --> 01:35:28,402
89.8067 degrees North...

693
01:35:28,526 --> 01:35:32,026
...and 221.5285 degrees...
Vasu!

694
01:35:34,693 --> 01:35:40,734
89.8067 degrees North.
And 221.5285 degrees East.

695
01:35:47,151 --> 01:35:51,026
Take a step forward to the Indian ship,
you will not return to your country.

696
01:38:29,068 --> 01:38:30,526
Are they really spooked?

697
01:38:31,943 --> 01:38:33,734
Yes. They all are terrified.

698
01:38:33,859 --> 01:38:36,193
I am pretty scared out here, too.

699
01:38:36,318 --> 01:38:40,318
Be careful.
If you slip, you have to keep going.

700
01:38:40,443 --> 01:38:42,276
There is no limit to the universe, dude.

701
01:38:42,402 --> 01:38:44,484
Hey! Don't scare me!

702
01:40:01,859 --> 01:40:04,693
You thought you could fight like a thug
and escape from here?

703
01:40:04,818 --> 01:40:07,235
Don't you need a plan
before attempting anything?

704
01:40:51,193 --> 01:40:52,693
Listen carefully!

705
01:40:52,818 --> 01:40:55,985
Escape to our ship
before their confusions clear.

706
01:41:49,151 --> 01:41:51,276
Come on!

707
01:41:55,318 --> 01:41:56,318
Captain! Behind you!

708
01:41:57,693 --> 01:41:59,151
Come soon and close it!

709
01:42:11,068 --> 01:42:12,068
Undocking Dhruva-1.

710
01:42:22,776 --> 01:42:24,443
Vasu hasn't come yet, Captain.

711
01:42:24,567 --> 01:42:25,901
We do not have any time!

712
01:42:26,026 --> 01:42:28,859
With the fuel we have,
we can run the engine for fifteen minutes.

713
01:42:34,193 --> 01:42:36,235
Come on, Vasu!
-Come on, dude!

714
01:42:40,026 --> 01:42:41,026
Hey!
-Come soon!

715
01:42:58,985 --> 01:43:00,443
His oxygen tank is leaking!

716
01:43:16,734 --> 01:43:17,734
Hey Vasu!

717
01:43:48,985 --> 01:43:51,151
Yes!
Thank God.

718
01:44:47,901 --> 01:44:48,985
Dad!

719
01:45:11,693 --> 01:45:12,693
He has made it!

720
01:45:18,985 --> 01:45:19,985
Running Engine A.

721
01:45:21,526 --> 01:45:22,567
Running Engine B.

722
01:46:08,854 --> 01:46:10,812
He needs an injection of adrenalin.
Hurry!

723
01:46:55,712 --> 01:46:56,712
Buddy!

724
01:47:25,629 --> 01:47:27,670
We've got the missile!

725
01:47:27,795 --> 01:47:29,379
The Chief will be glad
to hear this!

726
01:47:47,338 --> 01:47:51,670
Almost time for you
to hand over the missile to me.

727
01:47:51,795 --> 01:47:54,338
From here,
how can I give this missile to you?

728
01:47:54,462 --> 01:47:55,462
Dhruva-2!

729
01:47:55,587 --> 01:47:59,296
That's why I made you empty the fuel tank.

730
01:47:59,420 --> 01:48:01,254
What about my son?

731
01:48:01,379 --> 01:48:04,338
The minute you hand over
the missile to Dhruva-2...

732
01:48:04,462 --> 01:48:10,171
...your son will be safe with his grandpa
at the Army guest house in Munnar.

733
01:48:21,212 --> 01:48:22,629
Dhruva-2 is ready for docking.

734
01:49:18,503 --> 01:49:19,754
I have done what you asked.

735
01:49:32,629 --> 01:49:34,004
In another ten minutes...

736
01:49:34,129 --> 01:49:36,379
...your son will be safe
at the Army guest house.

737
01:49:37,670 --> 01:49:41,296
Do you know why I chose you
for this mission?

738
01:49:41,420 --> 01:49:43,129
Your love for your son.

739
01:49:47,004 --> 01:49:51,629
Neither you nor I are responsible
for those 40 million deaths.

740
01:49:51,754 --> 01:49:53,462
It was purely an act of nature.

741
01:49:53,587 --> 01:49:55,379
We couldn't stop it.
Simple as that.

742
01:51:01,379 --> 01:51:03,754
We have visual contact
with the asteroid's crater.

743
01:51:18,712 --> 01:51:21,795
Ten minutes left
to cross the safety line.

744
01:51:21,921 --> 01:51:24,338
Load the missile now, Swathi.
-Yes, Captain!

745
01:51:44,462 --> 01:51:45,545
The missile is missing!

746
01:51:50,296 --> 01:51:52,296
Only eight minutes
to cross the safety line!

747
01:51:55,962 --> 01:51:57,462
Is the missile ready for launch?

748
01:52:02,087 --> 01:52:03,587
What are you saying, Captain?

749
01:52:24,046 --> 01:52:25,338
Vasu's responsible for this.

750
01:52:29,712 --> 01:52:31,921
Look at the images
I'm sending over right now.

751
01:52:32,046 --> 01:52:33,171
He cut the fuel wire!

752
01:52:40,921 --> 01:52:43,629
He hid in plain sight
and betrayed our mission.

753
01:52:45,046 --> 01:52:47,212
He lies and cheats for a living.

754
01:52:47,338 --> 01:52:49,379
What else could we expect from him?

755
01:52:49,503 --> 01:52:52,129
Even if he is bad,
how could the missile leave the ship?

756
01:53:09,296 --> 01:53:11,503
Only one minute away
from the safety line.

757
01:53:13,587 --> 01:53:15,046
We came so close
to stopping it!

758
01:53:53,795 --> 01:53:55,212
It has crossed the safety line.

759
01:53:59,670 --> 01:54:01,087
The lives of 40 million people!

760
01:54:11,879 --> 01:54:13,795
Some of our families...

761
01:54:13,921 --> 01:54:15,171
...are in the target areas.

762
01:54:16,462 --> 01:54:18,254
We won't share details of the mission.

763
01:54:18,379 --> 01:54:21,046
Can you permit us
to speak to them one last time?

764
01:54:41,296 --> 01:54:44,296
Your son has been released, Vasu.

765
01:55:39,338 --> 01:55:41,338
Apologies for the delay
in telling you this.

766
01:55:41,462 --> 01:55:43,338
Missile is locked
and ready to launch!

767
01:55:45,670 --> 01:55:48,712
The asteroid hasn't crossed
the safety line. We have two minutes!

768
01:56:12,921 --> 01:56:14,587
In another ten minutes...

769
01:56:14,712 --> 01:56:18,171
...your son will be safe
at the Army guest house.

770
01:56:18,296 --> 01:56:19,795
Thank you, Vasu.

771
01:56:19,921 --> 01:56:21,795
If he's talking through this channel...

772
01:56:21,921 --> 01:56:24,629
...no one else must know of our plan,
until this is over.

773
01:56:33,129 --> 01:56:37,420
This is the exact design model,
of the missile that you have to steal.

774
01:56:38,420 --> 01:56:40,962
In space, one cannot tell the difference
in weight...

775
01:56:41,087 --> 01:56:44,171
...between a duplicate and the original.

776
01:56:47,795 --> 01:56:49,879
Load the missile now, Swathi.
-Yes, Captain!

777
01:58:54,587 --> 01:58:56,754
The suspense would've killed
the folks below!

778
02:02:43,587 --> 02:02:44,587
Dad!

779
02:03:00,087 --> 02:03:02,087
Look in your pocket!

780
02:04:16,503 --> 02:04:19,004
On our team's behalf,
here's a medal for you.

781
02:04:20,670 --> 02:04:21,670
Look in your pocket.

782
02:04:42,462 --> 02:04:43,962
After all, he is my son!

